IS  - 1
Y1  - 2013 Jan-Mar
T1  - A multidisciplinary approach to early mobilization of patients with burns.
SP  - 56-62
DO  - 10.1097/CNQ.0b013e31827531c8
AB  - Mobilizing patients with burns can be challenging due to their unique  characteristics. Many times, common practice is to elevate and immobilize the  burned extremity after debridement and grafting. On the contrary, mobility is  imperative for patients with burns, as patients can lose function and flexibility  quickly. The objective of this article was to review the current evidence related  to early ambulation in patients with burns as well as barriers to mobilization  within a burn intensive care unit. It also provides a demonstration of how a  nurse at the bedside in collaboration with a physical therapist can implement  these interventions and assist with early ambulation in patients with burns.
