TY  - JOUR
ID  - 19626932
VL  - 5
IS  - 207
Y1  - 2009 Jun 10
T1  - [Fall prevention: a challenge in the strategy of fracture prevention in the  elderly].
SP  - 1318-20, 1322-4
AB  - Fracture risk depends on density and quality of bone but also on fall risk.  Besides the resultant fractures, the human and socio-economic burden of falls  pose many challenges to the issue of prevention for the elderly. A systematic  approach to falls prevention should be considered as a part of routine care. The  identification of intrinsic and extrinsic risk factors is an essential initial  step to falls prevention. Intervention should be multidisciplinary and  multifactorial, targeting modifiable risk factors, especially for high risk  patients. We report the experience of a multidisciplinary program designed to  prevent falls and fractures, conducted at the Geneva University Hospital.
