Y1  - 1991 Nov-Dec
T1  - Multidisciplinary patient care in preventive dentistry: idiopathic dental pain  reconsidered.
SP  - 23-9
AB  - Pain is a complex phenomenon which challenges healthcare providers to develop  multidisciplinary diagnostic and treatment competencies. This paper reviews  literature on idiopathic odontalgia and tooth hypersensitivity without apparent  cause, and considers the role bioelectric mechanisms may play in the onset and  treatment of these moderately common disorders. The hypothesis considers that  such pain may be associated with health disturbances in areas remote from the  teeth and periodontium. A multidisciplinary approach to preventive dental health  is discussed along with factors which may impact the outcome in the treatment of  dental pain.
